I won't refund. I haven't even bought the game. I knew that it would be a mess. It's the new normal. Games always get released way ahead of time before they're even remotely finished.
What I usually do: Wait at least 1 year after release before buying a game. 
That way all the bugs, issues and immersion-breakage have been dealt with by the early adopters. 
That way I'll have a first time experience far greater than everyone else.

snippet.textDisplay: I know that Cyberpunk is rough on old consoles sometimes, but plenty of people are still having great experiences on them. I think the hate is a little overblown. I also think that people built the hype up in their own heads a little too much, them thinking it should was going to be a complete cyber-future sim. The rest of us just playing are enjoying leveling up our characters, and delving into the rich stories that Night City is full of. If people stop freaking out that its not perfect they could enjoy night city as much as I have.

snippet.textDisplay:
Cyberpunk running great on my 11 Tflop 1080GTX (soon to be upgraded to Radeon 6800XT).  Running at 50-60fps with optimized high settings at 1440p.  It looks great, but it feels eerily similar to Outer Worlds.  Weirdly similar at times.

Admittedly, I modded the config file and did the AMD SMT fix...but to be honest, it felt like part of the game.  Hacking to get an experience that console gamers cannot achieve is what PC Master Race is all about.

Long Live PC Master Race!!!!
